crimedata <- read.csv("/Users/l/Downloads/crimedata_csv_all_years.csv") %>%
  mutate(date = make_date(YEAR, MONTH, DAY)) %>% 
  group_by(date,TYPE) %>% 
  summarize(crimes = n()) %>% 
  ungroup(date, TYPE) %>% 
  complete(date, TYPE) %>% 
  mutate(crimes = if_else(is.na(crimes), 0, crimes)) %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = TYPE, values_from = crimes)

pmaxtemp <- joined_crimedata %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = max_temperature, y = `Other Theft`)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = 0.2) + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", aes(color = "Linear regression")) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  labs(title = "Other Theft vs Maximum Temperature",
       x = "Maximum temperature",
       y = "Daily cases of Other Theft",
       color = "Model")
print(pmaxtemp)

library(dplyr)
p2 <- tidy(reg2, conf.int = TRUE) %>%
  filter(term != "(Intercept)") %>%
  mutate(term = gsub("DayofWeek", "", term),
         term = gsub("MONTH", "", term)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = estimate, y = reorder(term, estimate), xmin = conf.low, xmax = conf.high)) +
  geom_pointrange() +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(title = "Estimate coefficients of various categories",
       x = "OLS estimate",
       y = "",
       caption = "Regression model that predicts incidence of Other Theft crimes")

print(p2)

cat("Based off the analysis, the estimate coefficient of various categories. It shows the type of crime 'Other Theft'  and the model predicts that the incident is more common on New Years and least on Christmas.")
Based off the analysis, the estimate coefficient of various categories. It shows the type of crime 'Other Theft'  and the model predicts that the incident is more common on New Years and least on Christmas.
